From Wiktionary, the free dictionary

Spanish

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

Borrowed from Latin interrumpere.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /interumˈpiɾ/ [ĩn̪.t̪e.rũmˈpiɾ]
  • Rhymes: -iɾ
  • Syllabification: in‧te‧rrum‧pir

Verb

[edit]

interrumpir (first-person singular present interrumpo, first-person singular preterite interrumpí, past participle interrumpido)

  1. to interrupt, to barge in, to disrupt, to disturb, to intrude, to cut in, to break in, to butt in
  2. to discontinue, suspend
  3. to cut short
  4. to break, to break off, to halt, to cease
  5. to stop (e.g., medication, treatment)
  6. to cut off, to block
  7. to heckle
